    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "### Problem\r\n\r\nAlthough the LSP provides the entire call hierarchy information, Neovim only displays references that are one level deep. Similar to vscode, the entire call hierarchy should be shown in a window allowing us to explore all the paths. There is an unmaintained [plugin](https://github.com/crusj/hierarchy-tree-go.nvim?tab=readme-ov-file) that used to address this issue.\r\n\r\n### Steps to reproduce using \"nvim -u minimal_init.lua\"\r\n\r\n```\r\n:lua vim.lsp.buf.incoming_calls()\r\n```\r\n\r\n### Expected behavior\r\n\r\nShould display a window showing the full call hierarchy\r\n\r\n### Neovim version (nvim -v)\r\n\r\nNVIM v0.9.2 Build type: Release LuaJIT 2.1.0-beta3\r\n\r\n### Language server name/version\r\n\r\ngolang.org/x/tools/gopls@v0.11.0 h1:/nvKHdTtePQmrv9XN3gIUN9MOdUrKzO/dcqgbG6x8EY=\r\n\r\n### Operating system/version\r\n\r\nmacos\r\n\r\n### Log file\r\n\r\n_No response_",
